                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 723.2515/116.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires at Santiago</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-03-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 26, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Government of the United States, through its Legation at Lima, has been
                    requested to undertake the protection of Peruvian <pb facs="1288" n="1184"
                        xml:id="pg_1184"/> citizens in Chile. The Government of the United States is
                    willing that its Legation exercise its impartial good offices in their behalf.
                    You will, if the Chilean Government consents, act accordingly during the
                    suspension of diplomatic relations. Repeat to Lima for information.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
